    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any of various international territorial divisions, typically a section of a county forming a unit of local government. In the United States, surveyed tracts of public land measuring 6 miles square and divided into 36 sections of 1 square mile each.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
